Cons: I feel that I read about this idea in the d20 Cthulhu book. I am not sure that a 2 meter electric fence is much of a deterrent, nor is 10 guards in junkyard uniforms. Why are they feeding it D class personnel? how does one electromagnetic crane patrol 1.5km of perimeter? A breach on two fronts would be uncontainable in any case. Flyovers to measure the perimeter? They didn't encounter the red sky? There are other problems as well, but I don't want to grind it down too much.

Pros:  This is perhaps the diamond in the rough. Make it a normal junkyard with clutter appearing from different eras, with failing combat cyborgs patching themselves with scrap. The picture is a keeper as well.

I agree with the previous posters, it is very similar to others. Dr Gravity summed it best; Not bad as first tries go,

I'd suggest taking it down then re-editing it into something more interesting.

